# Dashboard Chart Rendering — Implementation Plan

## Overview

Rich terminal chart rendering for `sentry dashboard view`, transforming
Sentry dashboard widget data into ASCII/Unicode visualizations that fit
the terminal width.

## Key Design Decisions

### Big Number Fonts
- 4-tier auto-scaling: XL (7×7) → LG (5×5) → SM (3×3) → single-line
- Font selection based on available width AND content height
- Vertical centering with ceil() bias (content sits slightly lower,
  looks better because title border draws the eye upward)
- Glyph fonts support digits 0-9 plus K and M suffixes

### Bar Charts — Color & Fill
- Color mode: SERIES_PALETTE (6 colors: magenta, cyan, yellow, green,
  blue, red) assigned per bar/series. "Other" always muted gray.
- Plain mode: PLAIN_FILLS (█, ▓, ▒) descending density fills.
  "Other" always gets ░ (lightest).
- Both categorical and stacked time-series bars use this system.
- Horizontal bars also use per-series colors.
- Legend markers: colored ■ in color mode, fill char in plain mode.

### Categorical Bar Labels
- Two-mode system after iterating through 3 approaches:
  1. ❌ Vertical text (one char per line) — unreadable kerning
  2. ❌ Horizontal wrapped text — unreadable for long labels
  3. ✅ Direct labels for short (fit barWidth) + letter-keyed legend for long

### Y-Axis
- formatTickLabel() using Intl.NumberFormat compact notation (321K, 1.5M)
- 3 tick positions: top (max), middle (max/2), bottom (0)
- Gutter width calculated dynamically from formatted max value

### Time-Axis
- Format adapts to span: <2d → HH:MM, 2-30d → MM/DD, >30d → Mon DD
- ┬ tick marks on axis line connecting to labels below
- Labels evenly spaced, clamped to prevent right-edge overflow
- Timestamps preserved through aggregation and downsampling pipelines

### Multi-Series Stacked Bars
- aggregateTimeseriesValues sums all series per time bucket
- renderStackedTimeBarRows pre-computes cumulative heights per column
- buildStackedColumn walks segments to assign correct color/fill per row
- buildSeriesLegend shows colored ■ / fill-char markers with labels
- Single-series widgets use the simpler single-color renderer

### Layout
- Framebuffer grid compositing matching Sentry's x/y/w/h widget layout
- Dynamic terminal width via process.stdout.columns (min 80, fallback 100)
- "Other" excluded from bar chart scale normalization to prevent
  dominating all real bars

## Iteration History

1. Started with sparklines and basic number display
2. Added framebuffer grid, proper data parsing, env/project filters
3. Added rounded borders, bar legends, adaptive big numbers
4. Added vertical bars, sorted categories, Y-axis ticks
5. Added large (5×5) then XL (7×7) big number fonts
6. Added compact Y-axis tick labels (formatTickLabel)
7. Tried vertical text labels above bars — too unreadable (kerning)
8. Tried horizontal wrapped text above bars — still unreadable for long labels
9. Settled on two-mode: direct labels for short, letter+legend for long
10. Added time-axis labels with ┬ tick marks
11. Added bottom axis lines on all charts
12. Added multi-series aggregation and stacked multi-color bars
13. Added per-bar colors (SERIES_PALETTE) and plain-mode fills (PLAIN_FILLS)
